 Season 1/2

Hiya all!

I'm new to this forum, and I must say that my first impression is "very cool". I've been watching Stargate for a while now because I got curious of the very first episode, Children of the Gods. Then I got stuck, because Stargate SG1 is a unique show with great actors! Of course Richard Dean Anderson is best, I like him from MacGyver. (which was also an awesome show!) I've only seen up to 2x10, so I don't know about the later seasons.

However, this show is exciting and very entertaining, it's not as Sci-fi as Star Trek, as it takes place at present time in an Air Force command center. I particularly like Teal'c, because I relate him to Star Trek: Voyager's Seven of Nine.

I'm looking forward to the later seasons!

Jaffa :P
